node.text: April is National Child Abuse Prevention month, and I’m proud to be working with @WoodwardCamp, who is committed to prioritizing safety within their camp experience. Woodward and I are working together to advance the camp’s child safety and health & wellness offerings through a number of different initiatives, including Woodward’s recent partnership with Prevent 360°. A collaborative prevention program from @D2Lorg and @mbfchildsafety , Prevent 360° aims to educate and empower campers, staff, coaches, adults and families to prevent abuse. Other than lots of gymnastics, we’ll also provide gardening, yoga, mental health education and other fun activities throughout camp. Visit the link in my bio for more information, and I hope to see you at camp this summer 😊🤍💙

node.text:
Beautiful gymnastics! The layout on beam is my favorite part. So so so stunning. In my opinion what makes someone incredible on beam is their ability to do the skills on the beam like they do on the floor. But because the beam is 4 inches wide & 4 feet tall it is easier said than done. This is what makes this routine so special in my opinion 🤍 
(I competed in this event final with her ☺️)

node.title: Deng Linlin 2012 Olympic beam final GOLD 🤍

node.text: @catalina_ponor has always been one of my favorite gymnasts. I loved watching her on beam & floor. I even used a piece of this music for my floor routine when I was younger because I loved her so much 😂 🤍 I also had the honor of competing with her... which was SO COOL 😊 Check out her beam routines too!
